## Behavior covered

- Existing phase-04 auth features F01-F04 were re-run with real logs rather than stale evidence.
- Register now creates a `confirm_email` email token using the existing `email_tokens` table.
- `/api/auth/confirm-email` validates an unexpired DB token and consumes it on success.
- Missing, invalid, expired, or already-consumed confirm-email tokens return 400.
- `/api/dev/reset-token` remains production-404 and can fetch `confirm_email` tokens only in dev/test.
- Login and forgot-password endpoints now have basic in-memory rate limiting.
- Session cookie is marked secure in production.

